            <p>You can associate multiple snippets with a stylesheet (or remove a stylesheet from those snippets). The procedure is similar to the one used for associating a stylesheet with master pages. You can open the File List window pane (<span class="Emphasis">View&gt;File List</span>), hold down your <span class="Emphasis">SHIFT</span>&#160;or <span class="Emphasis">CTRL</span> key to select the snippets, then right-click and choose <span class="Emphasis">Properties</span>. In the Properties dialog, select the <span class="Emphasis">Stylesheet Links</span> tab and choose your stylesheet, moving it to the right side of the dialog.</p>
